properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued December 31 at 1:36PM PST until January 2 at 12:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Large waves with hazardous surf expected.

* WHERE...North Coast and Central Coast.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to midnight PST Wednesday night.

* IMPACTS...Heavy surf can wash over beaches, jetties, and
breakwaters unexpectedly. People can be swept off rocks and
jetties and drown while observing high surf. Minor beach erosion
may damage coastal properties and buildings. Higher than normal
water run-up is expected on beaches and low-lying shoreline.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced swimmers should remain out of the water due to
dangerous surf conditions.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO MIDNIGHT PST WEDNESDAY NIGHT
